13:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Inflection and Microsoft Copilot share a solid foundation of core features including File Upload, Memory, Multilingual. Where Inflection pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Api Access, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. On the other hand, Microsoft Copilot uniquely offers Web Search and Code Execution and Image Generation and Voice Input and Plugins and Citations, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Inflection holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Microsoft Copilot scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
14:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, both Inflection and Microsoft Copilot offer flexible pricing models. Microsoft Copilot stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Inflection requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
