17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Inflection is best suited for enterprise, custom AI assistants, business workflows, productivity, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Microsoft Copilot, meanwhile, shines for Office 365 users, enterprise, Windows users, productivity, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Inflection describes itself as \"Enterprise AI platform by the creators of Pi.\" Microsoft Copilot, established in 2023, positions itself as \"Microsoft's AI assistant integrated across Office 365 and Windows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Microsoft Copilot** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0), more features (9 vs 4), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Inflection is a poor choice — far from it. Inflection excels in its own right, particularly for enterprise and custom AI assistants.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value deep microsoft 365 integration, go with Microsoft Copilot. If enterprise-grade security and reliability matters more to you, Inflection is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
